The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 World Briefs

 Bangla fugitive 

 Sylhet, March 1 (Reuters): Bangladeshi forces fired tear gas shells today and pumped water into a house in a northeastern town in an attempt to flush out the countrys top Islamist leader hiding inside, security officials said. 

 They were also planning to use tranquilliser guns to capture Shayek Abdur Rahman from the two-storey building in the town of Sylhet after his wife, detained earlier from the house, confirmed that the fugitive was inside. 

 Jordan riot 

 Amman (Reuters): Islamist prisoners loyal to al Qaida took a prison chief and six policemen hostage on Wednesday during riots at three Jordanian jails to stop the transfer of inmates convicted for killing a US diplomat, officials said. 

 Filipino ban 

 Manila (Reuters): Philippines President Gloria Macapagal Arroyo kept emergency rule in place on Wednesday as officials warned that many plotters were still at large. 




